          <div class="blogsingleheader">
           <h1>
            Spring Clean Your Diet with the Latest Food Trends!
           </h1>
           <!-- AddThis Button BEGIN -->
           <div class="addthis_toolbox addthis_default_style ">
            <a class="addthis_button_facebook_like">
            </a>
            <a class="addthis_button_tweet">
            </a>
            <a class="addthis_button_google_plusone" g:plusone:size="medium">
            </a>
            <a class="addthis_counter addthis_pill_style">
            </a>
           </div>
           <script src="https://s7.addthis.com/js/250/addthis_widget.js#pubid=ra-4fa29a3f6d840641" type="text/javascript">
           </script>
           <!-- AddThis Button END -->
           <p>
            <span class="boldby">
             By
             <a class="authorlink" href="http://www.alignedsigns.com/blog/author/AlignedSigns.htm" title="Read articles by Aligned Signs">
              Aligned Signs
             </a>
             (752 words)
             <br/>
             Posted in
             <a href="http://www.alignedsigns.com/blog/category/Diet.htm" title="view all articles filed under Diet">
              Diet
             </a>
             on
             <a href="http://www.alignedsigns.com/blog/2015/May/14.htm" title="view more artilces posted on May 14, 2015">
              May 14, 2015
             </a>
            </span>
            <br/>
            There are (
            <a href="#Comments" title="View Article Comments">
             0
            </a>
            ) comments
            <a href="http://www.alignedsigns.com/blog/Spring-Clean-Your-Diet-with-the-Latest-Food-Trends.htm" title="Spring Clean Your Diet with the Latest Food Trends! Permalink">
             permalink
            </a>
           </p>
          </div>
          <div class="blogtext">
           <p dir="ltr">
            <img alt="{#/pub/images/7632809_s.jpg}" height="232" src="http://www.alignedsigns.com/pub/images/7632809_s.jpg" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" width="349"/>
           </p>
           <p dir="ltr">
            Spring is the time of new beginnings! It is a good time to make
            <a href="https://www.alignedsigns.com/blog/Eat-Healthy-Stay-Healthy-Top-Foods-for-Wellness.htm">
             appropriate diet changes
            </a>
            to feel more active and full of energy.
           </p>
           <p dir="ltr">
            <span>
             Rather than going for drastic changes, it is a time to enjoy the fresh fruits and vegetables that hit the market, drink more water and add more unprocessed food in your diet. Here are a few tips.
            </span>
           </p>
           <ol>
            <li dir="ltr">
             <p dir="ltr">
              <span>
               Cook simple meals  You will spend more time in the kitchen. And you will be better off as you will cut down on packaged meals. Instead fresh whole foods to create simple dishes high in nutrients and low in calories. This way you avoid the extra sugar, sodium and fat of the processed food. Increase raw foods; these require more chewing and hence the brain is tricked into a feeling of fullness. Pound for pound, raw foods release fewer calories after digestion. They are
              </span>
              <a href="https://www.alignedsigns.com/blog/Fiber-is-an-Important-Part-Of-Your-Daily-Diet.htm">
               <span>
                high on fibre
               </span>
              </a>
              <span>
               too.
               <img alt="{#/pub/images/20680241_s.jpg}" height="217" src="http://www.alignedsigns.com/pub/images/20680241_s.jpg" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; float: right;" width="325"/>
              </span>
             </p>
            </li>
            <li dir="ltr">
             <p dir="ltr">
              <span>
               Manage your drinks  First, cut down on alcohol. Second, tank up on water. Cola and sweetened beverages need to be reduced. There are tastier and healthier options around. Your refrigerator should have enough plain water and sparkling water. It is a little known fact that dehydration can mask itself as hunger. So if you are not drinking enough water, chances are you will unnecessarily eat more. You can increase the intake of milk. To make your juices tangier, add a slice of lemon or orange. Mint leaves in water will also leave you refreshed.
              </span>
             </p>
            </li>
            <li dir="ltr">
             <p dir="ltr">
              <span>
               More soups, salads and smoothies  Spring is the perfect time for pureed asparagus soup. You add garlic and shallot to sauted asparagus before the broth. Then you let it simmer. Seasoning is upto you.
              </span>
             </p>
            </li>
           </ol>
           <p dir="ltr">
            <span>
             <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
             </span>
             4.At every meal, fill up half your plate with vegetables. Divide the remaining between grains and
             <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
             </span>
             lean meats.
            </span>
           </p>
           <p dir="ltr">
           </p>
           <p class="wys_textaligncenter" dir="ltr">
            <span>
             <br/>
            </span>
           </p>
           <p dir="ltr">
            <span>
             <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
             </span>
            </span>
            <img alt="{#/pub/images/19358389_s.jpg}" height="276" src="http://www.alignedsigns.com/pub/images/19358389_s.jpg" style="float: left;" width="219"/>
            <span>
             Make as many salads as you can with different colourful fruits and vegetables. Interestingly the
             <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
             </span>
             pigments which are responsible for color of fruits and vegetables are actually antioxidants. They help
             <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
             </span>
             fight stress. You can try a combination of strawberry and apricots with other salad ingredients. Or an
             <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
             </span>
             egg preparation which includes red bell pepper. Add the various berries to your smoothies.
            </span>
            <span>
             <a href="https://www.alignedsigns.com/blog/Juicing-A-Lifestyle-Change-for-a-Happy-Life.htm">
              Juicing
             </a>
             <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
             </span>
             <a href="https://www.alignedsigns.com/blog/Juicing-A-Lifestyle-Change-for-a-Happy-Life.htm">
              fruits
             </a>
            </span>
            <span>
             is an option too.
            </span>
           </p>
           <p dir="ltr">
            <span>
            </span>
            <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
            </span>
            5.Buy unseasoned meat  You can always at your seasoning of herbs. Try more of poultry and lean
            <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
            </span>
            meats than the processed variety; these will be fresher as well.
           </p>
           <p dir="ltr">
            <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
            </span>
            6.Green snacks  You dont want to be in a situation where you make the right effort at your
            <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
            </span>
            major meals but slip up when having snacks! So plan a little in advance about what you will have.
            <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
            </span>
            Again go for the fresher ones like eggs which you can prepare in various ways or combinations of
            <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
            </span>
            beans, yoghurt and vegetables. Also, you will not go wrong with options like raw nuts and plain
            <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
            </span>
            simple pop-corn!
           </p>
           <p dir="ltr">
            <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
            </span>
            7.Remove artificial sweeteners from your diet  Processed sugar adds empty calories which go to
            <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
            </span>
            your waist! It also encourages you to eat more. This Spring, cut out the processed sugar and replace
            <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
            </span>
            it with fructose in fruits and natural sugars in dairy products or even vegetables. Stay a strict No to
            <span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">
            </span>
            artificially sweetened yoghurt, juices, breakfast cereals and even pasta sauces!
           </p>
